Pieces of text such as the Hello World in print("Hello World!") are known as Strings.
Strings are just strings of text.

In writing print commands, you can add "\n" to print multiple statements like so:

print("Hello World\nHello World") and it will be printed 2 times.

print("Hello World\nHello World\nHello World") and it will be printed 3 times.

We can also add multiple strings. This is known as "Concatenation". We use "+" sign to do this.
Example:
print("Hello" + "Augustine")

print("Hello " + "Augustine") would leave a space between "Hello" and "Augustine" when printed
because we have left a space right after the word, "Hello" in the string.

